The 2009–10 &lt;a href="Toto%20Cup"&gt;Toto Cup&lt;/a&gt; Leumit was the twenty-eight season of the third most important &lt;a href="Association%20football"&gt;football&lt;/a&gt; tournament in &lt;a href="Israel"&gt;Israel&lt;/a&gt; since its introduction and sixth under the current format. It was held in two stages. First, sixteen &lt;a href="2009%E2%80%9310%20Liga%20Leumit"&gt;Liga Leumit&lt;/a&gt; teams were divided into four groups. The winners and runners-up, were advanced to the Quarterfinals. Quarterfinals, Semifinals and Finals was held as one-legged matches, with the Final played at &lt;a href="Winter%20Stadium"&gt;Winter Stadium&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href="Ramat%20Gan"&gt;Ramat Gan&lt;/a&gt;. The defending champions were &lt;a href="Hapoel%20Be%27er%20Sheva%20F.C."&gt;Hapoel Be'er Sheva&lt;/a&gt;, making it their third Toto Cup title overall.
It won on 15 December 2009 by &lt;a href="Hapoel%20Ironi%20Kiryat%20Shmona%20F.C."&gt;Ironi Kiryat Shmona&lt;/a&gt;.
Group stage.
The matches were played from August 8 to October 11, 2009.
